-->  Unlike servers, s3 will be replicated in every availibility zones in a specific region 
-->  High Availibility
--> Provides Versioning
-->  Three level of securities: SSE(Server side encryption) , KMS(Key management service) , Client side
--> Default : SSE     For more additional security: KMS
--> To give permission for an s3 bucket : make public using ACL ( Access control list) 
--> To delete any s3 bucket 1) delete objects (or) empty in bucket then delete
--> We can create multiple AWS S3 buckets using Terraform through for each.
Diff between locals and variables:
Input takes from user,easily override : Variables
For reuse of values,does not override  : Locals
--> We can store s3 buckets instead of  Nexus Repository to reduce the cost.
Storage classes:
  S3 Standard : Frequently accessed files ,Websites, applications, active data
  S3 Intelligent-Tiering: You don't know how often data will be accessed.AWS automatically moves objects between access tiers to reduce costs
  S3 Standard-IA: Backups,Disaster recovery files,Documents accessed occasionally
  S3 One Zone-IA: Re-creatable or non-critical data,Lower cost because data is stored in a single Availability Zone
  S3 Glacier Instant Retrieval: Medical records,Media archives that require immediate retrieval
  S3 Glacier Flexible Retrieval: Long-term backups,Compliance archives
  S3 Glacier Deep Archive: Records that are rarely accessed but must be retained for years,Lowest-cost storage option




